      <h2>{{title}}</h2>
      <p>Open-source projects are essential in modern software ecosystems, but as they grow, integrating business needs 
      can become challenging. To ensure timely development of new features, we've created the <b>Feature Request & Implementation</b> 
      Process. This process enables businesses, developers, and the community to collaborate on feature requests with 
      well-defined roles and timelines. It's designed to complement existing workflows and facilitate a seamless transition 
      from idea to implementation.</p>
      
      <h3>Motivation</h3>
      <p>This process bridges the gap between community-driven open-source projects and business requirements. By creating
      a clear structure for feature requests, businesses can contribute to projects without fragmentation, ensuring the
      longevity and sustainability of open-source communities.</p>

      <h3>Process Overview </h3>
      <p>The process is divided into three phases, each designed to help businesses and the community work together:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Request Phase</li>
        <li>Implementation Phase</li>
        <li>Finalization Phase</li>
      </ul>
